Note: Load balancing implementations
Process called "select_round_robin_node" that takes nodes as List[ComputeNode] returns ComputeNode:
    Return nodes[0]

Process called "select_least_loaded_node" that takes nodes as List[ComputeNode] returns ComputeNode:
    Let least_loaded be nodes[0]
    For each node in nodes:
        If node.current_load < least_loaded.current_load:
            Set least_loaded to node
    Return least_loaded

Process called "select_weighted_node" that takes nodes as List[ComputeNode] returns ComputeNode:
    Return nodes[0]  Note: Placeholder

Process called "select_adaptive_node" that takes nodes as List[ComputeNode] returns ComputeNode:
    Return select_least_loaded_node with nodes